12.  The objective of the women-specific initiatives under the Project is to provide vulnerable 
groups of women with the necessary resources, training, and skills to assist them to acquire a 
better economic and social status in their communities. This component focuses mainly on 
establishing a women’s business center, which would not only provide a secure environment for 
women entrepreneurs, but will also build up their capacity to conduct businesses of their own 
and enjoy the profits earned.  

13.  The beneficiary communities under this component will be selected according to the 
following criteria:  

(i)  percentage of female-headed households; 

(ii)  areas with the most number of viable enterprises; 

(iii)  number of displacements within the past ten years; 

(iv)  level of trauma experienced during recent years; 

(v)  poverty levels;  

(vi)  percentage of children under 10 years who show signs of malnutrition; 

(vii)  percentage of group participation and membership in established Women’s Rural 
Development Societies.  

14.  Beneficiaries will be selected according to the following criteria: 

(i)  female-headed households without any adult male wage earner; 

(ii)  inadequate housing; 

(iii)  average number of meals per family member per day; 

(iv)  number of children under 10 years who show signs of malnutrition; 

(v)  degree of willingness to participate in the program on a long-term basis. 

2.  Representative Subprojects 

15.  Representative subprojects to promote income generation, capacity building, and social 
cohesion include the following: 

(i)  Vocational  training—replicate  training  program  ongoing  in  Vavuniya  in  other 
districts,  addressing  microenterprise  development,  horticulture,  postharvest 
traditional food processing, and tourism service industry;  

(ii)  Vavuniya Cultural Center, Vavuniya district—construction of cultural center to be 
used for productions, exhibitions, meetings, and other large gatherings;

