(iii)  Faculty of Agriculture, Kilinochchi—develop master plan for phased construction 
of  destroyed  facility,  construction  of  initial  phase  for  most  important  facility 
components, including hostels for 100 students; 

(iv)  Livestock development—support artificial insemination centers, develop fodder 
production, provide animal quarantine facilities;  

(v)  Agricultural extension services—provide seed production farms, testing facilities, 
outreach activities;  

(vi)  Public market facilities—reconstruct damaged vegetable markets;  

(vii)  Inland aquaculture—develop inland fisheries in Kilinochchi;  

(viii)  Staff  quarters  for  government  employees—construct  four-apartment  housing 
units  for  government  employees  where  housing  availability  is  limited  or 
nonexistent; 

(ix)  Case  studies  and  prototype  programs  for  gender  enterprise  development—
provide skills training, technical know-how, marketing and profit-making skills, 
and gender-equity awareness to vulnerable groups of fishers’ war widows; and 
provide buildings to house businesses, including an administrative section and a 
community center where training and meetings will be held.
